column1: creating safety for ourselves is a lifelong endeavour i think. and it begins and ends with us.

creating a visual image we can turn to when we feel emotionally unsafe or our internal world feels overwhelming can be hugely helpful. we can turn to it when we need or bring it into our mindspace when we feel threatened to help calm our nervous system.

empower your own sense of safety in relationships. begin to create it for yourself and hold others accountable to your safety boundary. support others to uphold theirs. lets not settle for toxic behaviour
column2: damaging social media practices or unhealthy relationships. .

column1: i’m a b.a. in history with a concentration in afro-diaspora studies!  i served as a founding executive board member of 3 collegiate organizations
column2: one of which was officiated as a non-profit dedicated to providing a space to express authentic black womanhood and examine social injustices and issues from a lens of intersectionality. post graduation i was humbled to be acknowledged by the mayor of my hometown celebrating my service in the community and graduating with honors. i have served as a youth yogi
column3: and creative lead for a faith-based youth leadership academy and i am a certified master level kemetic reiki healer.

column1: 216068;instagram;2018-11-25 12:03:56;FALSE;"heute ist der internationale tag gegen gewalt an frauen. .
.ich habe im letzten jahr mein schweigen gebrochen und von meiner ersten ehe erzählt.
ich habe psychische gewalt erlebt. ich habe körperliche gewalt erfahren. ich bin fast umgebracht worden. aber:
heute habe ich keine angstzustände mehr
column2: keine flahbacks oder panikattacken. heute führe ich ein normales leben. zumindest sieht es von außen so aus. meistens glaube ich das sogar selbst.

column3: was ich erleben musste. diese unfassbare angst. .

column3: kann ich am ende vielleicht doch etwas gutes daraus werden lassen. .

column1: it's critical that we speak loudly about impunity which prevents this 'justice'. this conversation is too urgent to remain between the covers of our academic titles. so we invite you to be part of #exitimpunity.

column2: two projects — body of evidence and stepping stones — transform them into #theatre and #slampoetry through script-workshops and performances at universities
column3: law and medical colleges across india and nepal.

column1: in the next few months we'll be chronicling these and holding conversations across our social media channels. we will explore together what exactly impunity is
column2: how it plays out in the medical and legal systems
column3: and how we uphold it in our everyday lives.

column1: 216144;instagram;2018-11-25 11:25:36;FALSE;"* so your kid doesn’t have to heal from his childhood*
it’s a wonder when you see someone unencumbered going at life.

column3: and meet life’s fun and challenges lightly.

column2: they’re not triggered from what happened from their past
column3: they don’t go through life trying to get rid of a heavy past.

column1: that’s what i wish for us all.
but it’s harder for those of us who had it tougher.
i did not know much attachment parenting and all its benefits. i was babysat
column2: one of my first memories is when it was my 3rd birthday at my daycare. i went to preschool and everything
column3: saw the damage school can do like bullying and dumbing us down. i felt i had to go through life alone. i knew violence. all before my brain was fully developed at 25 like it does.

column1: at least it gave me the gifts of empathy
column4: the gold that holds my restored « japanese cup » together.

column1: and i’m not holding it against anybody (anymore). i guess most did the best they could at the time. it took me a looong time to heal. i finished recently
column3: i can be triggered at times.

column1: this is why i’m such a fan of good parenting.

column2: it shows. their parents are there for them (kids don’t feel alone)
column3: they shelter when their kids need it (kids don’t take full blows of life at a precocious stage)

column1: 💜hoy es el dia internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer. en 2018 llevamos 44 mujeres asesinadas en manos de su pareja. 266 mujeres en 15 años en españa. eso sin contar los menores también asesinados y los huérfanos.
mi apoyo a todas esas mujeres que han pasado (y están pasando) por este calvario.
que los amores que duelen no se conviertan en amores que matan.  confío en que podemos frenar la violencia machista aportando nuestro granito de arena.

column3: dengan meningkatknya kesadaran masyarakat dan pemangku kepentingan akan kekerasan seksual

column1: 216363;instagram;2018-11-25 08:29:10;FALSE;"internationella dagen för avskaffande av mäns våld mot kvinnor och flickor. denna dag angår oss alla. dig och mig.
detta inlägg skrevs strax innan jag erhöll bokkontrakt för min debutroman som beskriver mina erfarenheter.
en bok om våld i nära relationer. våld i hemmet. misshandel och våldtäkter.
vem ska läsa denna bok då?
svaret är: den majoritet som tror/tycker att detta inte är ett ämne som angår eller berör just er. alla som tror att detta är något som inte händer i deras närhet
column2: alla kvinnor som tror att det aldrig skulle kunna hända er.

column1: jag har varit en av er.
denna bok är också till de som redan vet
column2: de som kanske redan har varit där eller befinner sig där.

column1: till alla: anledningen till att våld i hemmet är något som fortfarande förekommer har samma botten som avgrundsvrålet #metoo väcktes ur. vi talar ogärna om obehagliga och obekväma ämnen som sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier
column2: inte heller våld i hemmet. förändringarna kommer. men de börjar ofta med vittnesmål
column3: berättelser. genom att belysa det ingen

column2: vetande. insikter och kunskap. jag hade kunnat bli mördad av min sambo innan jag fick uppleva min artonårsdag. anledningarna till att detta kunde förekomma är många och därför väljer jag att dela min berättelse

column1: till alla som tror att denna bok inte behövs
column2: till alla som tror sig redan veta
column3: till alla som inte vill veta och till alla som faktiskt redan vet. boken är till alla.

column1: 216411;instagram;2018-11-25 07:55:36;FALSE;"in the last few months i’ve indulged more of the anger i’ve stifled over the years than i have in a great long while. i’ve struggled to stay somewhere between the extremes — swallowing rage for the sake of keeping the peace and giving others the benefit of the doubt
column2: and unloading it as if no other person or feeling is more important than my own. most times it feels like mine is righteous anger. but i began learning very early in life that it was not safe for me to express anger or disagreement
column3: because it would make others “uncomfortable” and cost me relationships i valued. because no matter how much someone might truly be in the wrong
column4: in the end only i would be blamed and actually punished for expressing my needs or feelings about it. it seemed so unfair and yet an almost natural role i had to play to be the “bigger person” so i wouldnt end up lonely or disliked. only in retrospect do i recognize the people who truly care will not use abusive tactics to simultaneously constrain you in ways more convenient for them
column5: while magically absolving themselves of responsibility for their own less-than behavior.

column1: so i’m working on unlearning the fear struck into me by many abusive dynamics with friends
column3: and family. i’m learning to trust the truth in my anger more and to swerve on being gaslit
column5: and scapegoated. to swerve on anyone unwilling to pour love and mutuality into moments of conflict
column6: and to hold myself to that same standard.🌿

column1: 216447;instagram;2018-11-25 07:16:02;FALSE;"kekerasan seksual yang dialami seseorang memiliki berbagai macam dampak negatif hingga mempengaruhi kualitas hidup korban. dampak ini mencakup segi fisik

column2: upaya penanganan dan perlindungan korban masih belum sebanding dengan beratnya dampak yg dialami. rancangan undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual menjadi bagian dari upaya penguatan hukum yang sedang diperjuangkan untuk disahkan sebagai bentuk pencegahan dan penanggulangan kasus kekerasan seksual di indonesia.
aliansi satu visi sebagai aliansi yg mendukung pemenuhan hksr berupaya untuk meningkatkan kepedulian masyarakat terkait kekerasan seksual yang berdampak besar pada kesejahteraan dan kesehatan mental.
kami kembali menjadi mitra festival @enambelasffest dan mengadakan pemutaran film serta diskusi interaktif terkait kekerasan seksual. harapannya
column3: dengan meningkatknya kesadaran masyarakat dan pemangku kepentingan akan kekerasan seksual
column4: maka dapat mendorong terciptanya peraturan yang berpihak pada korban  dan mewujudkan masyarakat yang anti kekerasan.

column1: 216519;instagram;2018-11-25 05:27:20;FALSE;"⚠️warning: this may illicit an emotional response; feel free to look away or to respond accordingly—because i can respect how you feel.⚠️
even though in the past i believed “dirty little girls don’t get to eat”
column2: being shamed after completing yet another sexual act i was just forced into by an uncle at the age of 6
column3: spending a great majority of my life battling anorexia
column4: shaming myself for the various shapes and formations that my body took over the years before and after the births of my children
column5: questioning if the material shell was ever good enough to satisfy—or gratify—the men that came into and exited my life
column6: i see the correlation between the hateful words
column7: actions and paradigms that i “consumed and took into myself”
column8: and how they imprisoned me in that fearful child’s mind. i step forward into my future knowing that she has been set free
column9: and that i am an extraordinary specimen of love with a resilience that supersedes the fallacies of those memories and thinking
column10: and i will continue to live this life sharing hope
column11: love and light to all those that dare step into my extended
column12: loving arms; and i deeply and completely love and accept myself for who i am—and who i shall become. ~ruth a. muñiz

column2: upaya penanganan dan perlindungan korban masih belum sebanding dengan beratnya dampak yg dialami. rancangan undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual menjadi bagian dari upaya penguatan hukum yang sedang diperjuangkan untuk disahkan sebagai bentuk pencegahan dan penanggulangan kasus kekerasan seksual di indonesia.

column3: dengan meningkatknya kesadaran masyarakat dan pemangku kepentingan akan kekerasan seksual
column4: maka dapat mendorong terciptanya peraturan yang berpihak pada korban  dan mewujudkan masyarakat yang anti kekerasan.

column1: “what are you most grateful to yourself for?” this was a tough card to accept and i almost skipped. the whip card represents sexual abuse. why would i be grateful for something as horrible as that??
after pondering this for a few hours i realized i can be grateful because i’m a survivor. my mother can’t say the same. my aunts can’t say the same. my grandmother probably couldn’t either. with me
column2: the cycle was broken. i spoke up and continue to do so. i got proper counseling. i started a healing journey in 2011 that most likely won’t end until the day i die. i’m an advocate for women who have suffered trauma and abuse. and for that i must be grateful. thoughts @queenofheartstarot?

column2: november 25th 2018 is international day for the elimination of violence against women so i made the decision that today would be the day i would share my story. sharing this story is incredibly hard. the easy thing to do would be to forget it ever happened & never talk about it again
column3: especially not on an open forum. however
column4: i made a promise to myself to share my story so that we can start addressing this wide spread issue #metoo. it’s the right thing to do even if it feels so hard. which makes me think
column5: why is it so hard to share? for me it’s because it’s not normally talked about
column6: we live in a society even now where victim blaming still happens. i don’t want to feel like a victim all over again. i am not a victim
column7: i am a warrior. it almost feels forbidden to share my story
column8: why is this so? we were raised to hold it in
column11: don’t show ‘negative’ emotion. i have come to learn that emotion is just that
column12: not negative nor positive but essential for our existence whether it be sadness or happiness. it’s ok to feel sad & angry & actually important that we do so. we experience emotion to cope with the situation. so my gift from my experience is to share my story with the hope that i can make a change & perhaps help one person. would i go back and change it? no. it contributed to who i am today & that’s a strong
column13: determined woman with strong self worth and a mission to help where i can.

column1: 216591;instagram;2018-11-25 02:49:11;FALSE;"25 november marks the international day for the elimination of violence against women. the origin of this day goes back to 1960 when the three mirabel sisters from the dominican republic were assisinated  because of their resistance against state violence.
the stories we tell & amplify about who does anti-violence work matters. history matters. representation matters.

column2: ciswhitemale-centred and state-centred account of anti-violence work.

column1: we cannot eliminate violence against women: ⚡if cis-men are the voices of our campaigns
⚡ if we are 'partnering up' with the state (police
column2: child safety etc.) ⚡if we don't listen to and take the lead from first nations people ⚡ if we don't centre trans & gender diverse folk in our movements

column1: ⚡if we don't decriminalise and destigmatise sex work ⚡if we prioritise professionalism and middle class/respectability politics ⚡if we see certain bodies as too difficult or inconvenient ✨ honouring all survivors of violence today
column2: especially if your story has been left out of the public narrative. i hope to honour your survival and resistance
column3: even when it is deemed too difficult or inconvenient ❤️❤️❤️ ✨image is of the three mirabel sisters looking boss next to an old school car from the 1950s

column1: 216646;instagram;2018-11-25 01:43:53;FALSE;"voicestory is on shaw cable channel 4 on saturday night!
four great speakers sharing a moment of their lives with us
column2: so please take time and put away the phones and get a dose of inspiration and connection!

column1: at 11:00pm is carol metz murray & alison donaghey followed by eileen davidson & christine hylands at 11:30pm!

column2: experience their stories and then if you would like to connect with the speakers to ask any questions
column4: you can do so at our voicestory community here: www.facebook.com/groups/voicestory

column1: we thank you in advance for your help and support! 🙏❤️
here is an overview of their stories:
carol metz murray: the road-map of life is often covered by obstacles. carol discovered it matters not whether your life vehicle is a ferrari or a ford
column2: what matters is how you master driving life's road of self-discovery! life experiences can be the most excruciatingly wonderful
column3: relentlessly gentle life lessons with many possibilities!

column1: carol will share her experience of how you can discover that a wee-bit of insane courage can be the shift needed to open your heart to be all you can be!
alison was raped in high school and this impacts her perception of #metoo and ponders our need to think about things further
column2: as #metoo creates a polarization which creates an us vs. them situation.

column1: alison shares her story and her perspective that while social movements may seem attractive
column2: we must look deeper and really consider what we are supporting. we need to explore our accountability to move to a place of freedom.";;en;#mypart

column1: 216701;instagram;2018-10-23 03:04:47;FALSE;"there are forms of abuse so insidious
column4: that by the time we escape or they leave
column5: we are left in such a position that our experience goes unheard or disbelieved. we are broken or left with nothing
column6: often materially. this scenario is doubly common for children and gender oppressed peoples
column7: basically anyone who is oriented towards the other in such a way that their openness and desire for change can be contorted and used against them. .

column1: there is untold suffering all around us
column2: everyday we walk by abuse victims and survivors without knowing. only in a dehumanizing society is such interpersonal evil and silence possible. to end abuse we need to revolutionize the entire social system
column3: and this starts by connecting to those around us
column4: witnessing their suffering and rebelling against anything that should attempt to break our solidarity. #solidarity #healing #healingfromabuse #revolution #💜 .

the international day for the elimination of violence against women
column3: women in france held protests across the country to call for an end to violence against women. the protests are part of the #noustoutes — which translates to “all of us (women)” — movement

column1: the atlantic magazine calls this a “sex recession” and has devoted the coming december 2018 issue to explore the topic. a 12
column2: 665-word article tries to understand the main reasons for the phenomenon
column3: such as an overload of online entertainment that caused a decline in the desire for sexual intimacy
column4: the frequent use of dating apps which made flirting in public spaces less acceptable
column7: low self-esteem and sleep deprivation have all been suggested as reasons for suppressing the desire to have sex.

column1: add to this the high viewing rates of porn
column2: the #metoo movement that made men more anxious and less spontaneous about approaching women
column3: women’s growing fear of being exploited
column5: the social acceptance of getting married towards the age of forty
column6: the trend of living with one’s parents for economic convenience and avoid having children — and there you have a range of conditions that contributed to a major drop in sexual activity over the last two decades.

column1: but rather than seeing the decline in sexual activity as a mere problem
column2: we should see it as an evolutionary phenomenon that is now occurring in the human race.

column1: edit: the following incident happened just hours before i posted this picture (guess i found it on pinterest
column2: dm for credits). - it was almost 11pm & i was returning home from a friends house who lives nearby. my sister who was in gym at that time called me & told me to fetch a pizza on the way. i didn't have cash or card on me but the pizza place which is just behind my house shuts down at 11:30 pm so i went in & ordered two large pizzas & told the lady at the counter to keep it ready & i'll be back in 5mins w my card. went home
column3: got my card & when i was walking on the huge sidewalk(which also serves as a front space for pizza place & other shops) i saw two guys coming from the opposite direction. there was a lot of space on sidewalk & they were walking on the outer side while i was walking on the inner side. so i started tapping on my phone & next thing this guy pushed me. i felt his hand just below my tummy & he acted like it was just a light nudge & he wasn't looking up & all. he pretended as if there's a lot of crowd around
column4: he didn't see me walking his direction but in reality i had seen him walking far away from me & i knew his touch wasn't at all unintentional. so when i started creating scene by shouting at him
column5: he & his friend kept saying sorry & they just started running from there. . so don't tell me that ""when was last time you got molested on a sidewalk"" or anything like that. the saddest thing here was i couldn't run behind these guys since i had a leg injury & i was already walking weirdly(which i think he observed & that's why knew that i wouldn't be able to catch him if he ran) & there was no one around on sidewalk or road to help me. also i was angry at the pizza lady for not coming outside but then i left it there & moved on.  #feminist #breakthepatriarchy #metoo #metoomovement #believeinwomen #believeher #whydidntireport #whyididntreport";;en;#feminist

column1: queerness in the aftermath of trauma

how does one go about trusting a cis man when one’s body still bears bruises from the last one? no matter how different they said it would be – abuse and sex – i couldn’t extricate one from the other. the act would not be different
column2: so how could the effect be?
i wonder if i love women because i’m tired of being hurt by men. in effect
column3: i have the same question many queer survivors have: am i queer because i was abused? sometimes it upsets me because i don’t really know. maybe i am. maybe i’m not. i have found that most of the time

column1: the women i have loved have taught me what it actually is to “make love” and that is enough for me.
i don’t really care how i “got” queer
column2: i’m just happy to be here now.

column1: بسیاری از زنانی که دچار خشونت می‌شوند به دلایل متعددی حاضر به افشای آن نیستند. در برخی از جوامع کمتر توسعه یافته، خشونت مردان خانواده علیه دختران، همسران و مادران امری عادی تلقی می‌شود. در این جوامع برخی از انواع خشونت‌ها از سوی مردان از جمله خشونت‌های کلامی، کنترل‌گری، و یا جسمانی که فرد دچار آسیب جدی نشود، حتی میان زنان جامعه نیز به عنوان امری متداول پذیرفته شده است.

آموزش مصادیق خشونت و آگاه‌سازی جامعه می‌تواند قدم اول برای مهار خشونت باشد. درصورتی‌ که خشونت ادامه یابد، ترک فرد آزارگر در صورت امکان می‌تواند راه حلی برای این معضل باشد. گرچه در برخی جوامع بویژه جوامع کمتر توسعه یافته به دلیل عدم استقلال ذهنی و اقتصادی زنان، برای بسیاری از آنان ترک آزارگر امکان پذیر نیست.

آشکار کردن خشونت، شکایت به قانون و مراجعه به مشاور و روان شناس، از جمله رفتارهایی است که پس از بروز خشونت باید انجام بپذیرد.  سکوت در برابر خشونت نه تنها مانع تکرار خشونت از سوی آزارگر نمی‌شوند بلکه این امکان را به وی می‌دهند تا کار خود را تکرار کند.

آموزش مصادیق خشونت و آگاه‌سازی جامعه می‌تواند قدم اول برای مهار خشونت باشد. درصورتی‌ که خشونت ادامه یابد، ترک فرد آزارگر در صورت امکان می‌تواند راه حلی برای این معضل باشد. گرچه در برخی جوامع بویژه جوامع کمتر توسعه یافته به دلیل عدم استقلال ذهنی و اقتصادی زنان، برای بسیاری از آنان ترک آزارگر امکان پذیر نیست.

آشکار کردن خشونت، شکایت به قانون و مراجعه به مشاور و روان شناس، از جمله رفتارهایی است که پس از بروز خشونت باید انجام بپذیرد.  سکوت در برابر خشونت نه تنها مانع تکرار خشونت از سوی آزارگر نمی‌شوند بلکه این امکان را به وی می‌دهند تا کار خود را تکرار کند.

column1: as a woman in my (late) twenties in 2018 in paris
column3: here is what my experience has been so far. i haven't been the victim of physical or sexual violence. but a lot of people close to me (way more than i would have imagined) have. . .

column2: and then insulted when i didn't respond
column3: in the subway or in the street
column4: and i think 100% of the woman i talked about this with have as well. i even remember telling my mum that a guy had barked at me because i wasn't smiling at him
column5: and she replied it had happened to her just a few days before that...! . .

column1: i have been scared several times
column3: my hand around my keys in my pocket - in a poor attempt to be ready to defend myself if needed - by guys becoming a little too insistent and apparently not willing to take no for an answer. i remember the time a man reached out to feel up my breast
column4: just because he felt like it. and we're talking about france
column7: and open country. imagine what's happening everywhere else in the world... . .

column2: 2018 youtube channel #metoo published a powerful documentary called “ stories of sexual assault and abuse vol.1“ #metoo coined in october 2017. activist tarana burke founded the me too campaign in 2006
column3: but it did not take off until october 2017 when actresses started using the #metoo hashtag on social media to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment. it followed on the heels of the harvey weinstein sexual misconduct allegations in which the hollywood producer was accused of sexually assaulting 84 women
column4: many of whom were actresses and models. millions of women have used the feminist hashtag
column5: many also sharing their stories of how they have survived sexual violence or manipulation. it took the internet by such force and has brought the conversation about sexual harassment to the forefront.

column1: it’s so important that we share our stories and that we hold our attackers accountable! we tend to blame ourselves! we believe no one will believe us.. knowledge + awareness = prevention!

column1: 216994;instagram;2018-11-24 18:55:04;FALSE;"癲狂與過火的無賴電影，就是1980年代所謂港產片黃金時期的福星系列電影，從《奇謀妙計五福星》開始，大概是前無古人後無來者地以非禮女性為每一集的母題的電影。不論那五個福星是誰——包括《最佳福星》的劉德華——都以博懵為樂，在每一集中皆以「無傷大雅的玩笑」為包裝。不知那時候的女性觀眾怎樣想的，但這種混合性騷擾、動作、警匪和喜劇的電影的確是最賣座的主流（聽說在某些影評人建議這樣的「港產片」大可被獨立出來當一種cult的次類型，大概就是在於其剝削性與低俗）。若說是香港電影的「代表」，其實是scandalous的。
至於那些女星怎樣在戲外同樣遭受性剝削，就是另外的故事了。
